Prasanth &amp; Jose, 2014 A female with egg sac from Thenmala (pink form), dorso-retrolateral B female from Thenmala (blue form), dorsal C active burrows of juveniles on the road side mud embankment, Thenmala D active burrow of adult female on the forest floor, Kulathupuzha Forest Reserve. Photo credit Jimmy Paul.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="DA9BF448A068693F50328E4A764BABD0" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">
<paragraph id="D8C528C253E7D18930131751352D9144" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">
Figure 2. 
<taxonomicName id="819A42039A903152880CD47CF96BD3D4" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Haploclastus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haploclastus devamatha" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="devamatha">Haploclastus devamatha</taxonomicName>
