</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="85768FD41B9F1A203594BAC5843555CD" pageId="2" pageNumber="83" type="notes">
<paragraph id="65C4FCD822D5363EA2FF01FE48A0F098" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C343A7DC0B4E2AE5EE4BFDF6CB6FE89D" pageId="2" pageNumber="83">
Prasanth and Jose published their findings in January 2014, whereas Sanap and Mirza published their discovery in July 2014, so priority must go to the name 
<taxonomicName id="720348A8B9CA036F060590F4B12E098B" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Haploclastus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Haploclastus devamatha" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="devamatha">Haploclastus devamatha</taxonomicName>
and the name 
<taxonomicName id="29D813883BD847D2B5A6AA9932601CAA" class="Arachnida" family="Theraphosidae" genus="Thrigmopoeus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Thrigmopoeus psychedelicus" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="psychedelicus">Thrigmopoeus psychedelicus</taxonomicName>
becomes its junior synonym.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
